cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.HC 

The paper discusses computer vision algorithms and their similarities to the human visual system, suggesting that it is likely to fall under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of deep neural networks (DNNs) also suggests that it may fall under the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category. The comparison of human and DNN generalisation abilities suggests that it may also fall under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of behavioural consequences and the need for neuroscientists to search for mechanisms in the brain suggests that it may also fall under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
